{"type":"message","id":"842d617a","parentId":"abd2b916","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:57:05.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the problem clearly. The sessions.json references a path `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/product-selector/sessions/f3bca540-ab50-43ce-bd5f-8dd126caefe6.jsonl` but the actual file is at `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/f3bca540-ab50-43ce-bd5f-8dd126caefe6.jsonl`.\n\nAlso the session file only has 39 lines, and the last entry shows the conversation ended at around 1774613203993 (which is a very old timestamp - 2026-03-25 based on the file's creation date). The compactionCount is 0, meaning the session has never been compacted/summarized.\n \nLooking at the timestamp more carefully - 1774613203993 milliseconds converts to March 25, 2026, which aligns with the .reset file timestamp. The actual session file appears to be from that same date, and it looks like the conversation was reset rather than being an ongoing session.\n\nThe core issue is that the session file path in sessions.json points to `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/product-selector/sessions/f3bca540-ab50-43ce-bd5f-8dd126caefe6.jsonl` but the real file sits at `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/`. That's a path mismatch. Plus the product-selector agent has `runtime: \"subagent\"` configured, which could be causing it to spawn fresh each time instead of resuming from the existing session - that might explain why it's coming up blank. The path mismatch is the real issue here—the sessions.json file references `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/product-selector/sessions/` but the actual session file is stored under `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/`. This explains why the product-selector agent appears blank when it tries to resume, and why `/new` gets triggered. The question is whether this is a configuration bug or something that happened during the OpenViking migration, and I should verify whether the product-selector still has the same session path configured.\n\nLooking at the memory configuration, OpenViking is disabled so it's not handling memory management, and memory-lancedb is also disabled. That means the system is relying on the JSONL session files directly, which should work—but the path mismatch is breaking it. I need to check if this session ID was somehow migrated from a previous system state or if there's a misconfiguration in how the product-selector agent is resolving its session storage path."},{"type":"text","text":"音频暂时没法转文字，但我已经通过检查找到了问题的关键信息。让我直接回答你的问题：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ba5a8bb547cd40b6a107f773","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"date -d @1774613203993 2>/dev/null || python3 -c \"import datetime; print(datetime.datetime.fromtimestamp(1774613203993/1000))\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775811405015,"responseId":"0627ee4dab4a4ac4ba7ed3fb0ef80ced"}}
