{"type":"message","id":"1c2f0c4f","parentId":"dc1ac8bc","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:57:47.275Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. The product-selector agent's session (f3bca540) was last updated at 2026-03-27 20:06:43 CST\n2. The session file has only 39 lines (not very many)\n3. The sessions.json says the sessionFile is `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/product-selector/sessions/f3bca540-ab50-43ce-bd5f-8dd126caefe6.jsonl` but this path doesn't exist - only `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/f3bca540-ab50-43ce-bd5f-8dd126caefe6.jsonl` exists\n\n\n4. The timestamp difference is massive - 14 days ago versus today. This is definitely the core issue.\n\nLooking at the sessions.json, the sessionFile path is pointing to a non-existent directory, but the actual file lives under `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/`. This path mismatch suggests the configuration got corrupted when switching to OpenViking. There's also a memory-lancedb plugin that's disabled but present, and the OpenViking extension itself is disabled too.\n\nThe real problem is that product-selector is configured as a \"subagent\" with `runtime: \"subagent\"` and `spawnMode: \"run\"`, which means it runs in isolation with no shared context or memory. Every time it spawns, it starts completely blank because it's not inheriting anything from the parent session. The workspace directory points to `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace`, but that doesn't help if the underlying configuration is broken. The path mismatch suggests the sessions.json might be stale or pointing to the wrong location. Looking at the actual session data, the file at `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/f3bca540-ab50-43ce-bd5f-8dd126caefe6.jsonl` only has 39 lines from March 27, which is suspicious—either it's a very short conversation or something's off with how the session was recorded.\n\nThe real problem seems to be that when the product-selector agent runs as a subagent in \"run\" mode, each invocation starts from scratch with no memory of previous interactions, which would explain why users feel they have to repeat themselves constantly.\n\nThe core issue is that the subagent runtime doesn't maintain session continuity between runs—it's designed for one-off tasks, not persistent memory. For that, you'd need either \"session\" mode with thread-bound persistence, or a shared memory system like LanceDB that both the main agent and product-selector can access. Since LanceDB is currently disabled, there's no persistent memory layer at all, and the sessions.json file appears to have incorrect paths that don't match the actual agent configuration.\n\nThe most immediate fixes are either switching the product-selector to session mode if you want ongoing context, or re-enabling the LanceDB memory plugin to provide a shared knowledge layer that survives across subagent restarts."},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 问题定位到了，直接说结论：\n\n**当前存储方案**\n你的 product-selector Agent 用的是 **subagent 模式**（`runtime: \"subagent\"`, `spawnMode: \"run\"`），每次启动都是独立的新会话，没有持久记忆。\n\n**具体问题**\n1. **product-selector 的 session 上次更新是 3月27日**，之后就再没记录新会话了\n2. `sessions.json` 里的路径 `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/product-selector/sessions/...` 和实际路径不符（实际文件在 `agents/main/product-selector/sessions/`）\n3. 你的 `memory-lancedb` 插件是**关闭的**（`enabled: false`），所以向量记忆也没生效\n4. OpenViking 扩展也是**关闭的**（`enabled: false`）\n\n**为什么每次都是空白** → subagent 的 \"run\" 模式是一次性的，不保持跨会话记忆。需要改成 \"session\" 模式才会复用上下文。\n\n**下一步要做什么**——你想：\n- **A**：把 product-selector 改成 session 模式（保留对话上下文）\n- **B**：先启用 memory-lancedb（让记忆能跨会话召回）\n- **C**：两个都要\n\n确认一下方向我来改。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775811439626,"respo