{"type":"message","id":"763942b3","parentId":"d8244d8c","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:01:29.771Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to:\n1. Delete all product-selector sessions\n2. Change product-selector to use the same storage scheme as main agent (so it can remember context and store things properly)\n\nThe current product-selector config is in `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/agent/config.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"description\": \"选品专家 Agent - 负责产品筛选、市场调研、竞品分析、选品策略制定\",\n  \"capabilities\": [\"市场潜力评估\", \"竞品分析\", \"产品筛选\", \"数据驱动选品\"],\n  \"model\": \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\",\n  \"runtime\": \"subagent\",\n  \"spawnMode\": \"run\",\n  \"workspaceDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace\",\n  \"runTimeoutSeconds\": 300,\n  \"cleanup\": \"keep\",\n  \"expectsCompletionMessage\": true,\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-27T19:45:00+08:00\"\n}\n```\n\nThe key change needed is `spawnMode: \"run\"` → `\"session\"`.\n\nBut wait - I also need to understand how product-selector is actually configured in the agents list. Let me check the full openclaw.json to see if there's an agent definition for product-selector there, because from earlier when I searched for it, I didn't find it in the `agents.list` array.\n\nLet me re-check the openclaw.json agents list to understand how product-selector is defined and what needs to be changed.\n\nActually, from the sessions.json for product-selector, the key was:\n`agent:product-selector:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`\n\n\nAnd the config.json at `agents/main/product-selector/agent/config.json` is what defines the subagent configuration. But the user also mentioned OpenViking and the storage solution they configured - these are what enable persistent context and memory. So the real fix is changing spawnMode to \"session\" so the agent maintains state across interactions, and making sure the storage backend is properly configured to support that persistence.\n\nLet me check if there's a product-selector agent entry in the openclaw.json agents.list that I might have missed, since I only saw \"main\" when I searched earlier. If there's no separate entry, the product-selector might be a dynamically spawned subagent rather than a standalone agent. Either way, the core issue is ensuring the session storage and context persistence are working correctly so it remembers previous interactions and selections. I need to examine how product-selector is actually configured. It's defined in `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/agent/config.json` with runtime=subagent, but it's not appearing in the agents.list within openclaw.json. This suggests the product-selector might be spawned dynamically as a subagent rather than being a top-level agent definition. I should check if there's an openclaw.json.bak file to see what the previous configuration looked like and understand how this subagent was originally set up.\n\nLooking at the config more closely, it specifies `spawnMode: \"run\"` which means each invocation starts fresh. To enable persistent memory, I need to change this to `spawnMode: \"session\"` so it maintains context across interactions. I should also verify whether the session files are being stored in the correct location specified by the workspaceDir setting.\n\nFor storage, the agent relies on the session JSONL files written to the agents directory, and the compactionCount being 0 suggests compaction hasn't been triggered yet—which could mean the session data isn't being cleaned up or consolidated as expected. I need to clean up the session files and update the product-selector config to use session mode instead of run mode. The key change is switching spawnMode from \"run\" to \"session\" and potentially adjusting the model if needed. Since the user wants it aligned with main's storage approach, I should also verify whether product-selector is defined in openclaw.json or if it inherits settings from the main agent configuration. that key was `agent:product-selector:feishu:direct:...`, so the agent id is `product-selector`. And it had an entry in `agents/main/product-selector/sessions/sessions.json`.\n\nBut product-selector doesn't appear in the `agents.list` in openclaw.json. So it's not a registered agent in the traditional sense. It's probably spawned dynamically via `sessions_spawn` with `agentId: \"product-selector\"`.\n\nLooking at the main agent's tools config, I see it has `subagents` with `allowAgents: [\"*\"]`, so it can spawn any subagent. And it has `sessions_spawn` and `sessions_send` tools available.\n\nSo product-selector is a subagent that's spawned on-demand. The config in `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/agent/config.json` is what gets used when spawning it.\n\nTo fix the memory issue, I need to change spawnMode from \"run\" to \"session\" so it maintains state between calls, and I should also check the session storage configuration to make sure it's properly set up for persistence."},{"type":"text","text":"好，先删 session 文件，再改配置。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_64b01ca52771400ca04a1ac1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775811661628,"responseId":"0627ef4ec1feb73ede2e4a00553175a2"}}
