json` as separate agents rather than subagents, and since the user wants consistency, I should align their configurations so they both use the same workspace and session management approach. I need to figure out which config file is actually taking precedence here. The `agent/config.json` has `workspaceDir` while `openclaw.json` uses `workspace`, so they might be referencing different fields entirely. Let me just proceed with what the user asked: consolidate tts to use `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace` and enable session persistence instead of the one-shot run mode. I should also clean up those old session files while I'm at it.\n\nLooking at the openclaw.json structure, the tts agent doesn't have an explicit runtime or spawnMode specified, which might be why it's defaulting to subagent behavior. The product-selector seems to have its runtime explicitly set to subagent in its config, so there's some inconsistency in how these agents are configured. Rather than keep guessing at the config precedence, I'll make the changes the user requested and test to see what actually happens.\n\nThe user wants tts to use the same storage as main, but main is embedded while tts is subagent—these are fundamentally different runtimes. I should add session mode to tts's configuration to match main's context preservation, and update the workspace path to point to the same location so they're actually using the same storage backend."},{"type":"text","text":"好，两件事并行走：\n\n1. **删旧 session**（不影响，新的正常用）\n2. **改配置**：tts 的 workspace 改成和我一致，spawnMode 改成 session\n\n先备份再改：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3383dc2436064afa91be754a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cp /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json.bak.$(date +%Y%m%d%H%M%S)"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ed69eaa224b64f448081ccc3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"rm -f /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/sessions/f3bca540-ab50-43ce-bd5f-8dd126caefe6.jsonl && rm -f /home/halei/.open