{"type":"message","id":"ef66a2c0","parentId":"37778d3d","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:05:26.557Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants the tts (product-selector) agent to have the SAME storage scheme as me (main agent). They want independent storage but with the same storage mechanism. Let me re-read what this means.\n\nThe main agent's storage:\n- workspace: `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace`\n- Sessions are in: `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/`\n- It uses the main workspace for files\n\nThe tts agent currently:\n- workspaceDir: `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-selector`\n- Sessions in: `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/`\n\nThe user wants tts to have the SAME storage scheme as main. By \"same storage scheme\", they probably mean:\n1. Use the same session storage location/pattern (session persistence in agents/xxx/sessions/)\n2. Not necessarily the same workspace directory\n\nActually, I think the user means: keep tts's workspace separate (workspace-selector), but make sure the storage/session mechanism is the same - i.e., session persistence works properly.\n\nWait - but the tts already has proper session storage in `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/`. It's working fine. The sessions.json shows the tts agent has an active session from today.\n\n\nThe config currently has workspaceDir pointing to the main workspace after my earlier edit. The user wants the tts agent to keep its own independent workspace at workspace-selector, but maintain the same storage architecture - the session files in agents/tts/sessions/ with sessions.json tracking them properly. So I need to revert workspaceDir back to workspace-selector while ensuring the session storage mechanism stays consistent with how the main agent manages its sessions. 我需要撤销之前对workspaceDir的修改，恢复到workspace-selector，因为用户想要独立存储但使用相同的存储机制。tts的sessions目录已经配置正确了，我只需要确保workspaceDir保持独立。"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了，你要 tts 保持独立 workspace，但存储机制和我一样。那